original: Ernander, Tyra Maria, ämneslärarinna, Uddevalla, f. 29/8/91 i S-thlm av und :löjtn. P. O. Ernander o. Anna Maria Charlotta Sörrnan. Stud:ex. i Upps. 10, fil. mag. där 16, provår v. Gbgs h. latin 20-21. Vik. lär. v. Rrs-bergska sk. i Örebro 16-17, i Söderhamn 17-18 O’, i Leksand 18-19, lär. v. Lundens ka privat sk. i Gbg 19-20, e. o. ämneslär. v. Uddevalla prakt, mellan-isk. 21-22, ord. ämnesl-är. i modersm., hist. o. geogr. där sed. 22.
translated: Ernander, Tyra Maria, subject teacher, Uddevalla, born on August 29, 1891 in South Stockholm to Lieutenant P. O. Ernander and Anna Maria Charlotta Sörrnan. She received her high school diploma in Uppsala in 1910 and earned her Bachelor of Arts degree there in 1916. She completed her probationary year in Latin at Gothenburg's upper secondary school from 1920-1921. She was a substitute teacher at Rrs-bergska school in Örebro from 1916-1917, in Söderhamn from 1917-1918, and in Leksand from 1918-1919. She was a teacher at Lundens private school in Gothenburg from 1919-1920, and an assistant teacher at Uddevalla practical preparatory school from 1921-1922 before becoming a permanent subject teacher in Swedish, history and geography in Uddevalla from 1922 onwards.
